<H3> <TI>   Teaching Contingent Receives Anniversary Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Teaching Contingent Receives Anniversary Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1504005994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1504005994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro, first secretary of 
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba and 
president of the Councils of State and Ministers, sent a message 
to the Third Manuel Ascunce Domenech Teaching Contingent, urging 
the contingent to continue defending the Revolution's 
achievements. 
  The letter was sent on the occasion of a provincial ceremony 
in Pinar del Rio commemorating the contingent's 20th 
anniversary. Education Minister Luis Ignacio Gomez was present 
at the ceremony. 

</TEXT>

