<H3> <TI>   Government `Source' on NATO Bombings of Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government `Source' on NATO Bombings of Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1604173094 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1625 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1604173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 16 Apr (DPA) -- A Cuban Foreign Relations 
Ministry source said today that the NATO bombings of the Bosnian 
city of Gorazde could trigger serious consequences for the 
Balkans, Europe, and the rest of the world. 
  The governmental Radio Rebelde reported that the diplomatic 
source maintained that the air attacks could spark unexpected 
consequences at regional, continental, and world levels, instead 
of contributing to reaching a fair solution of the conflict. 
The source of the Cuban Foreign Ministry believes that the path 
to peace must not follow an escalation of war, not even as a 
result of a foreign military intervention. On the contrary, all 
parties should refrain from encouraging this alternative; they 
should take definite steps toward promoting the success of the 
negotiation efforts and the attainment of a political agreement 
that would bring peace to that region. 

</TEXT>

