<H3> <TI>   Says Havana Seeks Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Havana Seeks Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1704024994 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0007 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1704024994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina said in 
Asuncion, the capital of Paraguay, that in response to the 
severe economic blockade imposed by the United States, his 
country is in need of an economic model characterized by 
openness to trade and foreign investment. 
  During a news conference on the second and final day of his 
working trip to Paraguay, Robaina said that one of the main 
reasons for his South American tour was to advertise investment 
opportunities on the island. 
  During Robaina's trip to Paraguay, several political leaders 
from the South American country called for the restoration of 
diplomatic ties between the two nations, which were broken 
during the sixties because of pressure from the United States on 
the Paraguayan Government. The request was made by Senators 
Carlos Romero and Eugenio Zanabria, both members of the ruling 
Colorado Party [National Republican Association] and Manuel 
Benitez, leader of the Authentic Radical Liberal Party, the 
foremost opposition party. 
  The Cuban foreign minister is concluding in Paraguay a tour 
that included official trips to Uruguay, Peru, and Argentina. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

