  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina today began a 
two-day unofficial visit to Paraguay. The first working day 
began with a meeting with acting Foreign Minister Oscar Cabello, 
with whom he exchanged ideas on the future of the Common Market 
of the South and on the reality of and prospects for Cuban 
development. Robaina also met with the Public Health Committee 
of the Chamber of Deputies of Paraguay, whose members recently 
visited Cuba and demonstrated interest in our country's 
biopharmaceutical development. 
  Roberto Robaina also met with the main leaders of the 
various 
parties in Paraguay. He met with Dr. Manuel Benitez Florentin, 
of the Authentic Radical Liberal Party; Eugenio Sanabria, 
president of the Colorado Party; Guillermo Caballero Vargas, 
president of National Encounter [as heard]; and Senator Victor 
Sanchez, president of the Febrerista Revolutionary Party. 
  Another important meeting was that between Roberto Robaina 
and Carlos Romero Pereira, acting president of the Senate, who 
was accompanied by several members of the Senate Foreign 
Relations Committee. 
  Later in the evening, Foreign Minister Robaina met with the 
Asuncion Municipal Council and mayor at the Paraguayan-Japanese 
Center. 
  Tonight [16 April], Robaina is scheduled to be interviewed 
by 
Bruno Massi of Paraguayan television's Channel 9. 

</TEXT>

