<H3> <TI>   Power Outages To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Power Outages To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1504231994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1933 GMT 
15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1504231994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 15 April, the Electric Union of the Ministry of 
Basic Industry announced that the electric power deficit being 
experienced nationwide will continue on into next week, and that 
outages will continue to be extensive. The nation's power 
generation capability is 3,132 megawatts, but the fact that the 
generator units of certain plants have not received maintenance 
or have broken down has resulted in a significant drop in the 
output of energy. Although 1,325 megawatts were provided this 
week, there is a marked difference between the nation's supply 
of electricity and its demand. This has resulted in extensive 
outages between 0500 and 0000. 
  Next week's deficit is estimated at 680 megawatts; 
therefore, 
the extensive outages will continue. 

</TEXT>

