<HT>    "drlat074_a_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-074 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lage Views Sugar Harvest in Eastern Provinces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lage Views Sugar Harvest in Eastern Provinces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1504185594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1504185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Carlos Lage Davila, vice president of the Council of 
State, has urged sugar industry workers throughout the country 
to continue exhibiting the same spirit in the final stage of the 
harvest. 
  During the assessment of the current sugar harvest in the 
southeastern region, Lage presented to Granma the banners 
acknowledging the province as the best of three during the first 
10 days of April. Reporter Jorge Luis Batista has a recording by 
Lage on this matter: 
  [Begin Lage recording] A political message of a sugar 
harvest 
that is beginning to recover is a very positive political 
message, one that helps and encourages us to tackle the 
situation and to confront the daily difficulties. 
  I don't know whether I need to make a call for a final 
effort, because the appraisal that we have from all comrades is 
that the maximum effort is being made. The call must be to 
maintain that maximum effort during this harvest, because this 
is what will bring the nation resources, although these 
resources will be very limited because the harvest is still 
limited. Nevertheless, I am leaving with the conviction that the 
three provinces being assessed will fulfill their objectives -- 
especially Granma, because I had the opportunity to listen to 
the directors of the different complexes and I think the people 
are making the efforts that are necessary for the Revolution. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

