<H3> <TI>   Reports on Le Borgne `Shoot-out' Still `Confusing' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Le Borgne `Shoot-out' Still `Confusing' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1504213194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1504213194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Haiti Press Agency, AHP, the 
situaton remains confusing in the northern Haitian village of Le 
Borgne following a shoot-out that took place last weekend 
between a number of armed civilians and a number of military 
from the Le Borgne outpost. The Haitian military authorities 
have yet to make public any official version of the incidents in 
Le Borgne. 
  AHP says that reports by Inter Press Service mention several 
people being killed during the attack, without specifying which 
side suffered the alleged losses. AHP reports, further, that a 
number of sources, which coincide, make mention of many arrests 
in the Le Borgne area, including that of Le Borgne mayor 
Belizaire Fils-Aime and a rural policeman. Several houses were 
also reportedly burned down. 
  It should be noted that there is no telephone link between 
Port-au-Prince and Le Borgne. 

</TEXT>

