<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Professional Army Formation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister on Professional Army Formation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1504214194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1857 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1504214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 14 Apr (NA) -- Interior Minister 
Carlos Ruckauf said today that a professional Army "represents a 
mid- or long-term possibility" and ruled out the possibility of 
Argentina being able, at this moment, to implement "this type of 
project." 
  Thus, Ruckauf discussed the possibility of replacing the 
current compulsory military service system with a professional 
Army. He nevertheless refused to make any additional comments 
because this issue does not specifically involve his portfolio, 
but the Defense Ministry. 
  The interior minister stressed: "An unrestricted dignity 
must 
be guaranteed for those drafted." He added that conscripts 
"must not be petty soldiers, but qualified soldiers in order to 
defend our fatherland." 
  In remarks to journalists accredited to the Government 
House, 
the interior minister pointed out: "In my opinion, General 
(Martin) Balza's quick handling of such a delicate situation is 
very significant." 

</TEXT>

