<H3> <TI>   Jujuy Governor Resigns; Perassi To Stay Until 1995 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jujuy Governor Resigns; Perassi To Stay Until 1995 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1504145894 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1019 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1504145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador de Jujuy, 15 Apr (NA)--Jujuy Province 
Governor Jose Carlos Ficoseco, who was on a six-month leave of 
absence, resigned his post early this morning after Judge Mario 
Gonzalez issued a writ depriving Ficoseco of his rights. 
  Ficoseco's resignation was submitted early today to Oscar 
Perassi, parliamentary secretary of the local legislature. 
Perassi, who assumed the governorship on the night of 13 April, 
will now remain in his post until 1995, when a new governor will 
be elected in the general elections. 

</TEXT>

