<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Debt Agreement Closed in New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debt Agreement Closed in New York </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1604004494 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2300 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1604004494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After three years of negotiations, Brazil has closed 
its foreign debt agreement. The country will pay $51 billion 
over 30 years, representing a 30 percent discount. A maneuver 
by the Brazilian negotiators thwarted threats by the Dart 
family, which holds Brazilian foreign debt papers and does not 
agree with the discount. The Dart family was threatening to 
file an international lawsuit against Brazil for failure to pay. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

