<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Surcharge on Chinese Textile Products Extended </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Surcharge on Chinese Textile Products Extended </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1504214894 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1824 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1504214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 14 Apr (AFP-NA) -- It was officially 
reported today that the Chilean Finance Ministry has extended 
the enforcement of the 18 percent surcharge on Chinese textile 
products. 
  The measure aimed at protecting the local textile industry, 
which is facing a crisis of low prices because of an abundant 
and inexpensive supply of foreign textile products, affects 18 
fiber, wool and cotton manufactured products. 
  The Chilean Government has stated that the surcharge on 
Chinese textile products may be increased once a study 
establishes the extent of direct and indirect subsidies received 
by the Chinese textile and clothing industry. 
  Chilean Textile Union Leader Manuel Bustos, who is currently 
president of the United Labor Confederation, has said that some 
Chinese companies have a zero-cost hand labor because people 
serving judicial sentences are used as forced labor. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

