<F P=106> [Bulletin issued by the Mexican National Defense Secretariat </F>
on 15 April; place not given; from the "24 Hours" newscast] 
  [Text] At approximately 0530 today, the military checkpoint 
established near Tuxtla Gutierrez on the road to Chicoasen was 
attacked with gunfire by a small group of unidentified 
civilians. The shots were fired from a distance of approximately 
200 meters, wounding a sergeant of the signal corps. He was 
evacuated to the regional military hospital in Tuxtla Gutierrez 
where he later died. 
  The armed attack lasted until 0620. It was repulsed by the 
military personnel who forced the attackers to flee. It is not 
known whether the attackers sustained casualties. The civilian 
population was not harmed. 

</TEXT>

