<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Deputies Stripped of Political Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Deputies Stripped of Political Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1404235994 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 14 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PY1404235994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With 297 votes in favor and 116 against, the Chamber 
of Deputies on 13 April stripped Deputy Carlos Benevides 
(PMDB-CE) [Brazilian Democratic Movement Party-Ceara] of his 
political rights. In the morning, with 346 votes in favor and 42 
votes against, alternate Deputy Feres Nader (PTB-RJ) [Brazilian 
Labor Party-Rio de Janeiro] also was stripped of his political 
rights. He cannot become a deputy nor run in the next elections. 
Benevides and Nader were both involved in the budget scandal. 
  President Itamar Franco on 13 April sanctioned a law 
approved 
by the Senate that increases from three to eight years the term 
during which members of Congress are deprived of their political 
rights when found guilty of a lack of decorum. 

</TEXT>

