<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Presidential Spokesman Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Presidential Spokesman Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1504002894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1653 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1504002894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 13 Apr (EFE) -- The Planalto Palace Press 
Office reported that Brazilian President Itamar Franco today 
appointed journalist Fernando Jose da Costa as the new 
presidential spokesman, replacing Francisco Baker. 
  Da Costa is a 58-year-old employee of the state-owned radio 
and television network Radiobras [Brazilian Radio Broadcasting 
Company]. He has served as deputy to Baker for the past 18 
months since Franco's inauguration. 
  Baker resigned as Franco's spokesman last month to take a 
top 
position in communications at the IMF in Washington. 

</TEXT>

