<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Joao Domingos] </F>
  [Text] Alcantara -- The PT [Workers Party] government will 
give priority to programs like that of the Alcantara Rocket 
Launch Center. This is what PT candidate Luiz Inacio Lula da 
Silva said on 13 April to Aviation Colonel Jose Celso Lauande, 
the center's commander, who met Lula to show him the way the 
project is operating. The project has been fully developed with 
Brazilian technology. 
  Lula, who started another stage of his Caravan of the 
Citizenry in Maranhao, carefully listened to Lauande's briefing. 
To help him ask the colonel questions, Lula was accompanied by 
Reserve Colonel Geraldo Cavagnari, who helped the PT design its 
program for strategic areas and advanced technology. The PT 
candidate showed his indignation at the fact that the center 
needs $40 million to operate at full capacity. Of the center's 
total cost of $260 million, $117 million remains to be provided, 
for which reason the space program has been considerably delayed. 

</TEXT>

