<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Jorge Bastos Moreno] </F>
  [Excerpt] Brasilia -- Former Finance Minister Fernando 
Henrique Cardoso has practically secured the support of the main 
PMDB [Brazilian Democratic Movement Party] dissidents for his 
presidential candidacy. In a secret political negotiation, in 
which President Itamar Franco himself participated, Cardoso 
obtained the support of the so-called Rio Grande do Sul group, 
which is led by Senator Pedro Simon. This group is against the 
alliance between the PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy Party] and 
the PFL [Liberal Front Party]. 
  Cardoso also obtained a promise from ex-President Jose 
Sarney 
to support his candidacy as soon as the internal PMDB elections 
reveal stronger support for ex-Governor Orestes Quercia. Recife 
Mayor Jarbas Vasconcellos and some PMDB candidates to state 
governorships will work for Cardoso's candidacy after the PMDB 
internal elections. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

