18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1804183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] DPRK President Kim Il-song has stressed that the 
DPRK has neither the intent nor the capacity to produce nuclear 
arms. That would make no sense, he said, adding that the United 
States is mistaken in thinking that pressure and intimidation 
can bring the DPRK to its knees. 
  This statement was made by Kim Il-song in the course of an 
exclusive PRENSA LATINA interview at the Presidential Palace. 
During the two-hour interview, Kim Il-song addressed the current 
tense situation being experienced by the DPRK, relations with 
the PRC and other countries, foreign investment, and the outlook 
for reunification of the Korean peninsula. 
  Kim Il-song also praised the DPRK's ties with Cuba and 
President Fidel Castro. In a measured and firm voice, Kim 
Il-song stressed that his government is committed to turning the 
Korean peninsula into a nuclear-free zone. 

</TEXT>

