<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Colombia and Cuba confirmed their bilateral 
relations in the sports field with the signing of a two-year 
sports agreement which includes the exchange of coaches, and 
information on sciences applied to sports. Luis Alfonso Munoz, 
general director of the Colombian Institute for Youth and 
Sports; and Conrado Martinez Corona, president of the National 
Institute for Sports, Physical Education, and Recreation, signed 
the agreement in the presence of Jose Ramon Fernandez, vice 
president of the Council of Ministers. 
  In a news conference with the accredited press, Munoz 
stated: 
It is the most important agreement that Colombian sports has 
ever made with a country with as much tradition and experience 
as Cuba. Munoz went on to say: We are talking about the first 
country of America in sports and the fifth in the Olympic Games 
of Barcelona. I believe the sports movement of my country can 
benefit from Cuba's important achievements in the field of 
sports. 

</TEXT>

