<F P=102>   FL1804234494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1804234494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Angolan graduates from Cuban education centers last 
week in Luanda celebrated a day of solidarity with Cuba on the 
33d anniversary of the Playa Giron victory. 
  Victor Nataniel Narciso, vice president of the association 
of 
former Angolan students in Cuba, has urged the United States to 
lift the economic and commercial blockade imposed on the island 
for more than three decades. He said this blockade is the main 
cause of the complex economic situation in Cuba. 
  A baseball game was played yesterday as part of the 
celebration, between members of the Cuban diplomatic mission and 
members of the Angolan association. This game is considered 
historical as the first match of this nature played in Angola. 

