  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro has expressed the 
willingness of Cuba's people and government to expand and 
strengthen their ties of friendship and cooperation with 
Zimbabwe. 
  On 15 April, Castro, who is president of the Councils of 
State and of Ministers, sent a letter of congratulations to 
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe on the occasion of the 14th 
anniversary of Zimbabwe's independence, which is observed on 18 
April. The letter points out that the Cuban people admire the 
enormous efforts made by the fraternal nation of Zimbabwe to 
promote the well-being of its people, who face resolutely every 
difficulty obstructing their economic and social development. 

