<F P=102>   FL1804144794 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1804144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 17 April, militiamen and reserve troops promotion 
and award presentation ceremonies, as well as regional defense 
system exercises, were held as part of Havana's defense day in 
tribute to the Giron victory. The ceremonies were held in 10 de 
Octubre, Guanabacoa, and El Cotorro Municipalities. 
  Jorge Lezcano, member of the Politburo and president of the 
provincial defense council, and Brigadier General Samuel 
Rodiles, a member of the Central Committee and deputy chief of 
the Western Army, were in attendance. 
  At the ceremony in Hermanos Gomez Polytechnical School, 10 
de 
Octubre Municipality, Lezcano stressed the praiseworthiness of 
the thousands of Havana residents who are, in the midst of 
severe economic limitations, preparing militarily to save the 
fatherland and the Revolution. 

</TEXT>

