<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Chairs Anniversary Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Raul Castro Chairs Anniversary Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1604181894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1604181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces, chaired the national ceremony 
marking the 33rd anniversary of the proclamation of the 
socialist character of the Revolution and combatants day. More 
than 6,000 people participated in the popular gathering where a 
military review was held. The review was brightened with 
patriotic poems and songs as well as typical elements of the 
national culture. 
  The Mariana Grajales Plaza of the Revolution in Guantanamo 
City also served as the site for the promotion ceremony of 
reservists and combatants and the decoration of combatants that 
served important missions along the perimeter that borders the 
Yankee naval base. The occasion also served to award outstanding 
people and institutions, with a replica of Maximo Gomez's 
machete for their excellent work in the cultural field. The 
ceremony was held outside of La Fortaleza de la Cabana for the 
fist time. 

</TEXT>

