<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Sends Letter of Recognition to Canecutters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Raul Castro Sends Letter of Recognition to Canecutters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1804235194 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2220 GMT 
18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1804235194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces, has sent a letter of recognition to 
members of the the Roberto Rodriguez brigade of volunteer 
canecutters for their achievements in the current harvest. This 
brigade is cutting cane in Camaguey Province, which was awarded 
millionaire status in the manual cutting of sugarcane. 
  In the province of Camaguey, 25 brigades of canecutters have 
managed to cut one million arrobas during the current harvest, 
while another group is on their way to cutting a third million. 
Considering these results, Camaguey has obtained the status of 
millionaire in manual canecutting. 
  [Begin unidentified worker recording] All comrades here are 
willing to cut to the last sugarcane for this harvest. This 
shows that victory is achieved when there is the willingness and 
desire to fight for this Revolution and to bail the country out 
of its current situation. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

