<H3> <TI>   Human Rights Agreement Signed With Guatemala </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Human Rights Agreement Signed With Guatemala </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1604010894 Mexico City UNOMASUNO in Spanish 11 Apr 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PA1604010894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City UNOMASUNO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jorge Madrazo Cuellar, president of the National 
Human Rights Commission (CNDH), and Guatemalan Human Rights 
Ombudsman Jorge Mario Garcia Laguardia yesterday signed a 
cooperation agreement to conduct research, exchange information, 
and publish material which supports the work of institutions 
devoted to the defense, promotion, and respect of human rights 
in Mexico and Guatemala. 
  The CNDH reported specific actions to be conducted by the 
respective ombudsmen include courses on human rights, 
cooperation, exchange of information and experiences with 
similar institutions in other countries, and research and 
attention to Mexican and Guatemalan immigrants' problems 
regarding human rights. 

</TEXT>

