<H3> <TI>   Information Exchange Accord Signed With Costa Rica </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Information Exchange Accord Signed With Costa Rica </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1904032394 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2046 GMT 14 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1904032394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 14 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- The National 
Foreign Trade Bank (Bancomext) and the Chamber of 
Representatives of Foreign Enterprises (Crecex) have signed an 
agreement to exchange information on statistics and customs 
duties systems. 
  Bancomext issued a communique stating that it will make 
arrangements for Crecex to access Bancomext information to 
locate foreign trade business opportunities through its Foreign 
Trade Service Center [Centro de Servicios de Comercio Exterior]. 
The Costa Rican organization will provide information on the 
demand for Mexican products in that Central American country and 
on biddings by public and private organizations, as well as 
everything regarding the customs duties system and foreign trade 
statistics. 
  This first agreement was signed within the framework of 
NAFTA 
to strengthen and broaden economic relations between Mexico and 
Costa Rica and to contribute to regional development. Bancomext 
Assistant Director Humberto Molina Medina and Crecex President 
Gerardo Loria signed the agreement during a visit to this 
country by a group of Costa Rican businessmen. The objective of 
the visit is to contact Mexican suppliers of chemical, plastic, 
and pharmaceutical products, printing paper, and auto parts. 

</TEXT>

