<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Injuries Reported in Mail Service Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Injuries Reported in Mail Service Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1804210094 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1544 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1804210094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 18 Apr (NA) -- A regular-intensity 
bomb exploded at a private mail service in this capital's 
Chacabuco Park area early this morning. No injuries were 
reported. 
  The explosion took place at the headquarters of the firm 
Transclair SRL at 1222 Cobo Avenue, near the corner of Centenera 
Street, at around 0100 local time. It damaged the establishment 
and adjoining buildings. 
  According to reports by neighbors, the attack is said to be 
the result of a "trade war" between companies engaged in the 
same trade. 
  One of the company managers, Antonio Gomez Dolzer, said: "We 
have received telephone threats for a long time. Some shots 
were even fired at the front of the building four months ago." 
  For reasons of jurisdiction, police Precinct No. 12 is 
conducting an inquest into this case. Federal Police bomb squad 
personnel were called when the explosion occurred. 

</TEXT>

