  [Text] Two journalists have been arrested by the Ministry 
of Government. They have been identified as Edith Munoz and 
David Garcia, both of whom have been charged with having alleged 
ties with terrorism. 
  [Begin recording] [Minister of Government German Quiroga] 
The 
court investigations are about to be concluded. In keeping with 
what is established in the law, they were able to see their 
relatives on 18 April, 24 hours after their arrest, particularly 
the woman in question. 
  This afternoon the police will be instructed to allow the 
press access to those arrested and tomorrow they will be placed 
at the disposal of the courts. 
  We have established that they were very closely involved in 
the killing of the Mormons, especially the woman. Therefore, we 
are conducting investigations in this direction. 
