<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Backs Creation of World Trade Organization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Backs Creation of World Trade Organization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1504155094 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0130 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1504155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Peruvian Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Efrain 
Goldenberg, who is in Morocco, today expressed optimism about 
the decision to create the World Trade Organization. 
  Goldenberg is heading the Peruvian delegation that is 
participating in the GATT conference. Goldenberg said that the 
World Trade Organization, which will be created after the 
conclusion of the GATT conference and will supervise world 
trade, is the outcome of the liberalization policy advocated by 
Peru. 
  Regarding the so-called social clause advocated by the 
United 
States and several European countries, Goldenberg was against 
mixing the labor jurisdiction of the International Labor 
Organization with the trade jurisdiction of the future World 
Trade Organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

