<F P=106> [From the "Seven O'Clock Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] The peace agreements with the Socialist Renewal 
Movement [CRS] will give the former guerrillas the possibility 
of putting two members into the Chamber of Deputies for the 1994 
to 1998 term. CRS leaders went to Narino Palace today. 
  President Cesar Gaviria and the former CRS guerrillas made 
official the peace agreements today. For the first time, the 
former guerrillas entered Narino Palace to announce to the 
country that from now on they will be a political alternative 
within the law. This is the fifth guerrilla movement to set 
aside its weapons during the past six years to reach a peace 
agreement. 

