<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palmero Lauds Agricultural Feats of Havana Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palmero Lauds Agricultural Feats of Havana Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1904151794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1904151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 18 April, Candido Palmero, member of the 
Politburo and first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in 
Havana, said that the province will harvest 2 million quintals 
of potatoes. During a farewell ceremony for the Giron de 
Victoria unit, Palmero praised the organization, discipline, and 
productivity of the unit which, in only 45 days of work, 
harvested approximately 700,000 quintals of potatoes and over 
34,000 quintals of miscellaneous crops. The unit has some 2,000 
military and civilian members. The Giron de Victoria unit 
planted approximately 30 caballerias of tubers and vegetables in 
addition to tending another 32 caballerias. 
  The Giron de Victoria unit also conducted outstanding social 
work in schools and small towns in the municipalities of Guines, 
Batabano, Melena del Sur, Guira de Melena, San Antonio de los 
Banos, Alquizar, and Quivican. At the farewell ceremony, several 
workers received the production and defense combatant medal and 
the status of outstanding in defense. 

</TEXT>

