<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Monde Consults Chamber of Commerce on Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Monde Consults Chamber of Commerce on Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1904183994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1904183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 18 April, within the scope of the parliamentary 
plan that has already received the support of the United States 
and the United Nations, Frantz Robert Monde, president of the 
Chamber of Deputies, began his consultations with employers in 
order to resolve the crisis. Both Monde and Max Villard, vice 
president of the Haitian Chamber of Commerce and Industry, 
deemed those talks very positive. 
  According to the president of the chamber, the two officials 
tackled the core of the problem: the executive vacuum and how to 
fill it. Villard renewed the employers' support for the 
parliamentary plan for the resolution of the crisis. This plan, 
which provides for the installation of a new prime minister 
after the retirement of General Raoul Cedras, but does not set a 
date for the return of Jean-Bertrand Aristide, has been rejected 
by the president-in-exile. 
  On 13 April, Monde criticized President Aristide for his 
stubborn refusal to appoint a new prime minister and announced 
that he wanted to initiate consultations on fill the executive 
vacuum. Deputy Monde labeled this meeting as fruitful, but 
refused to reveal the points discussed. 

</TEXT>

