<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Le Borgne Mayor Reportedly Released After Arrest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Le Borgne Mayor Reportedly Released After Arrest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1904192394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1904192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A correspondent working in the north of Haiti 
announced on 18 April the release of Le Borgne Mayor Belizaire 
Fils-Aime, who was arrested in connection with the armed attack 
against the police station there by armed individuals. The 
situation is very tense in Le Borgne and the arrival of military 
reinforcements coming from Cap-Haitien, Fort-Liberte, and even 
Gonaives was noted. No one can provide explanations of what 
actually happened because of the fear of the people living in Le 
Borgne. This area is listed among the main areas of tenseness 
since the events of 30 September 1991. 

