<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Constitutionality Court President Takes Office </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Constitutionality Court President Takes Office </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1904192694 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 15 Apr 
94 p 87 </F>

<F P=103> PA1904192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gabriel Larios Ochaita took office as 
Constitutionality Court (CC) president in a ceremony at the 
court's hearing room at 1900 last night. 
  The ceremony began with the singing of the national anthem 
followed by a minute of silence in memory of Epaminondas 
Gonzalez Dubon who was CC president until Good Friday [1 April), 
when he was assassinated. 
  In his speech, President Ramiro de Leon Carpio said his mind 
and heart were filled with two conflicting feelings regarding 
memories of Gonzalez: The first memory is his participation as 
president of the Commission of 30, which drafted the 
Constitution, and his role as alternate president of the 
National Constituent Assembly, which issued the current 
Constitution; and the second memory is his regrettable and 
painful death. 

</TEXT>

