<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Unions Reject IMF Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Unions Reject IMF Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20657C </F>
<F P=103> 94P20657C </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
CSO 

    [Editorial Report] Managua BARRICADA in Spanish of 5 April 
1994 on page 5 reports that Jose Espinoza Navas, leader of the 
Permanent Congress of Workers, and Lucio Jimenez, National 
Workers Front leader, expressed their reluctance to support the 
IMF agreement which provides for the Enhanced Structural 
Adjustment Facility. They stated: "We are not going to back with 
our signature something which will harm the already precarious 
situation of the workers." Espinoza said that union leaders were 
"extremely concerned" because the agreement threatens the jobs 
of 15,000 workers. Espinoza and Jimenez explained that the 
threat of huge layoffs will determine whether the union leaders 
participate further in talks with the High Level Commission 
studying the agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

