<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1904191294 </F>
<F P=103> PA1904191294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Panama's economic developments monitored through 19 
April. 
  During the first quarter of 1994, Panamanian exports rose by 
4 percent in comparison with the same period of 1993. So far 
this year, Panamanian exports have totaled $74.7 million, while 
in 1993, exports for the same period amounted to $71.9 million. 
(Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 13 Apr 94 p 11A) 
  The Panamanian Foreign Trade Institute has reported that 
Panama's annual export income from fishing operations last year 
exceeded $85 million, which represents more than 18.2 percent 
from the previous year's exports. Shrimp exports alone amounted 
to $60 million, second only to the $200 million derived from 
banana exports. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1757 GMT 16 Apr 94) 

</TEXT>

