<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Says Import Taxes To Decrease </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Says Import Taxes To Decrease </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2004000494 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2004000494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Rubens Ricupero today said he will 
further lower import taxes to make internal prices drop. He said 
that whomever commits price abuses will have to compete with 
cheaper and perhaps better-quality products. Ricupero favors 
putting the real into circulation as soon as possible but did 
not specify a date. He also supports the conversion of foreign 
debt titles to finance education projects. Such a conversion 
already is being applied to social and environmental projects. 
  Minister Ricupero also said that he trusts in the economic 
program's success, even though some economic sectors still are 
not operating in URV's [Real Value Unit]. This week he will 
announce the form of conversion for postal fees. 
  Minister Ricupero today met Deputy Tarcisio Delgado, leader 
of the PMDB [Brazilian Democratic Movement Party] in the Chamber 
of Deputies, and told him that Congress should establish in the 
Constitution only the general principles of the tax and social 
security reform. The rules for these reforms, the minister said, 
should be defined through complementary laws. 

</TEXT>

