<F P=100> Venezuala </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Caldera on Constitutional Amendments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Caldera on Constitutional Amendments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1604162794 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1604162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Rafael Caldera has emphasized that 
constitutional amendments must include provisions for an 
impeachment referendum, that is, the possibility that people 
could impeach any government official, including the president, 
who fails to perform his duties. He made these statements at the 
opening of a play called "Venezuela, Political Crisis, and 
Constitutional Reforms." He also said that participative 
democracy must be the main aspect of the amendments to ensure 
that people will have a say in the nation's important 
sociopolitical issues. He also rejected all doubts that the 
community will not be able to understand the amendments due to 
the large number of articles. 
  [Begin Caldera recording] People will not discuss the 
amendments article by article; they will merely reply yes or no, 
as is done in every democratic country. They will ratify or 
reject the amendments drafted by the National Congress. [end 
recording] 
  He also said that it is necessary to give the Venezuelan 
people a greater opportunity to participate and more power in 
view of the situation the country is currently experiencing. 

</TEXT>

